Boundary-offset uniform dark-matter zoom example.

This example starts from the UniformDMGravity ICs, applies a half-box offset
to all particle coordinates in the IC file so the high-resolution distribution
straddles all periodic corners, then uses ``InitialConditions:shift`` to move
particles by +0.5 in each axis before zoom-region recentring is applied.

Run with the --zoom runtime option.
